<p>Often the phrase “Fixing the phase” or “Flipping the phase” (or more correctly, “Flipping the polarity”) is used in audio production. <em>What does that mean</em>? Why would you attempt to do that? When should you look for problems? How do you do it?</p>

<p>I’m going to try and cover these questions starting from the very basics. This includes scenarios without physical recordings, so you electronic musicians may get something out of it too!</p>

<p>Let’s get started.</p>

